                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4593: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul in Charge at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-09T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 9—9:49 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sun left Canton on British warship today at 4 p.m. for Hongkong where he plans to
                    transship to <hi rend="italic">Empress of Russia</hi> for Shanghai. Local
                    situation quiet. Sun forces defeated in north Kwangtung.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
